            <div class="largeImageLinks">
            <p><em>Updated 6/27/2016</em></p>
<p>This privacy policy governs your use of the software application&nbsp;Daytona International Speedway (&ldquo;Application&rdquo;) for mobile devices that was created by&nbsp;AVAI Mobile on behalf of Daytona International Speedway, LLC (&ldquo;DIS&rdquo;). The Application is&nbsp;a tool containing important and useful information about the Daytona International Speedway (&ldquo;Speedway&rdquo;) and its events. You can find important race-day information, view maps, connect to social media and navigate your way the Speedway.</p>
<p><b></b></p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">What information does the Application obtain and how is it used?</h4>
<div></div>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">User Provided Information</h4>
When you use the Application, you may choose to provide us with your email address and to subscribe to emails from us through the &ldquo;E-mail Sign-Up&rdquo; section of the Application. We do not collect any other user provided information through the Application.
<p><strong></strong></p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">Automatically Collected Information</h4>
In addition, the Application may collect certain information automatically, including, but not limited to, the type of mobile device you use, your mobile devices unique device ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, the type of mobile Internet browsers you use, and information about the way you use the Application.
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">DAYTONA Rewards Program</h4>
If you elect to register for participation in the DAYTONA Rewards program through the Application you will be required to provide your name, email address, phone number, zip code, date of birth and event attended, and you may be asked to provide additional optional information (collectively, &ldquo;DAYTONA Rewards User Provided Information&rdquo;). We may share DAYTONA Rewards User Provided Information with DIS sponsors for sponsors&rsquo; promotional messaging purposes, including but not limited to Toyota Motor Sales, U.S.A., Inc., Sunoco, LLC, General Motors, LLC and Memorial Health Systems, Inc. d/b/a Florida Hospital Memorial Medical Center. DIS is not responsible for how sponsors use DAYTONA Rewards User Provided Information. Please see sponsor&rsquo;s privacy policy for more information on how the DAYTONA Rewards User Provided Information will be used by the sponsor.
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">Does the Application collect precise real time location information of the device?</h4>
<p>When you use the Application, we may use GPS or Bluetooth technology (or other similar technology) to determine your current location in order to properly display your location on the Speedway maps or to send you geo-based promotional alerts. All location information collected by us is anonymized and/or aggregated so we will never use the location information to locate you or any other specific individual. See Terms of Service for more information on this feature. If you do not want us to use your location for the purposes set forth above, you should turn off the location services in your mobile phone settings or uninstall the Application.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">Do third parties see and/or have access to information obtained by the Application?</h4>
<p>Yes. We will share your information with third parties only in the ways that are described in this privacy statement.</p>
<p>We may disclose User Provided Information, Automatically Collected Information and DAYTONA Rewards User Provided Information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>as required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process;</li>
    <li>when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a&nbsp;government request;</li>
    <li>with our trusted services providers who work on our behalf, do not have an&nbsp;independent use of the information we disclose to them, and have agreed to adhere&nbsp;to the rules set forth in this privacy statement;</li>
    <li>if&nbsp;we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a&nbsp;portion of its assets, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our Web site of any change in ownership or uses of this information, as well as any choices you may have regarding this information.</li>
</ul>
<p>Additionally, third party developers hired by us to develop the Application and its functions are permitted to collect Automatically Collected Information only in anonymized or aggregated form for the purposes of providing analytics reporting to us, and to improve the Application and their other products.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">What are my opt-out rights?</h4>
<p>You can stop all collection of information by the Application easily by uninstalling the Application. You may use the standard uninstall processes as may be available as part of your mobile device or via the mobile application marketplace or network. If you&rsquo;ve subscribed to our emails each email you receive will contain opt-out information for email communications.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong>Children</strong></h4>
<p>We do not knowingly market to or collect personal information from anyone under 13 years of age through the Application. If we become aware that we have unknowingly collected personal information from a child under the age of 13, we will make commercially reasonable efforts to delete such information from our database.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong>Security</strong></h4>
<p>We are concerned about safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. We provide physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect information we process and maintain. For example, we limit access to this information to authorized employees and contractors who need to know that information in order to operate, develop or improve our Application. Please be aware that, although we endeavor provide reasonable security for information we process and maintain, no security system can prevent all potential security breaches.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong>Third Party Sites</strong><strong></strong></h4>
The Application offers links to other sites or mobile applications including without limitation Facebook, Google, YouTube, Instagram and Pinterest. These third party sites or applications have their own policies regarding privacy. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third party sites or applications and cannot guarantee the security of any of your personal information collected, used or shared there.
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong>Changes</strong></h4>
<p>This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. We will notify you of any changes to our Privacy Policy by posting the new Privacy Policy&nbsp;here in the Application and, if you enrolled for email communications, through email. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is deemed approval of all changes. </p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong></strong></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"><strong>Your Consent</strong></h4>
<p>By using the Application, you are consenting to our processing of your information as set forth in this Privacy Policy now and as amended by us. "Processing,&rdquo; means using cookies on a computer/hand held device or using or touching information in any way, including, but not limited to, collecting, storing, deleting, using, combining and disclosing information, all of which activities will take place in the United States.&nbsp;If you reside outside the&nbsp;United States your information will be transferred, processed and stored there under United States&nbsp;privacy standards.&nbsp;</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;"></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;">Contact us</h4>
<p>If you have any questions regarding privacy while using the Application, or have questions about our practices, please contact us via email at <a href="mailto:daytonaspeedway@daytonainternationalspeedway.com">daytonaspeedway@daytonainternationalspeedway.com</a>. Daytona International Speedway, LLC., 1801 W. International Speedway Blvd., Daytona Beach, Florida 32114.</p>
	
            
